This paper proposes a hierarchical reinforcement learning (HRL) structure for autonomous vehicle planning tasks, which involves learning multiple sub-goals simultaneously and reusing well-trained networks for similar tasks. This work involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for decision-making, robotics (RO) for autonomous vehicles, machine learning (LG) for the HRL structure, control systems (SY) for behavior planning, and computer vision (CV) for perception systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.CV.
